main event: Unidentified flying objects were observed visually and by radar at Marine Corps Air Station El Toro, California, from 11 to 12 November 1956.
interesting points: Radar detected objects with estimated speeds ranging from 500 to 15,000 mph,Multiple witnesses observed the same phenomena visually and on radar,NULL visual confirmations for many radar sightings,The sighting events spanned over several hours with attempts to intercept the objects failing,Analysis suggested local phenomena could have affected radar performance.
witness description: Military personnel including pilots and radar operators, experienced in aircraft and radar operations.
